class DDSetDebugger: Debugger implementing the DDSET algorithm for abstracting failure-inducing inputs.

__init__(self, grammar:Dict[str, List[Union[str, Tuple[str, Dict[str, Any]]]]], generalizer_class:Type=<class '__main__.TreeGeneralizer'>, parser:Union[fuzzingbook.Parser.Parser, NoneType]=None, **kwargs:Any) -> None: Constructor. `grammar` is an input grammar in fuzzingbook format. `generalizer_class` is the tree generalizer class to use (default: `TreeGeneralizer`) `parser` is the parser to use (default: `EarleyParser(grammar)`). All other keyword args are passed to the tree generalizer, notably: `fuzzer` - the fuzzer to use (default: `GrammarFuzzer`), and `log` - enables debugging output if True.
__repr__(self) -> str: Return a string representation of the generalized call.
fuzz(self) -> str: Return a call with arguments randomly instantiated from the abstract failure-inducing pattern.
fuzz_args(self) -> Dict[str, Any]: Return arguments randomly instantiated from the abstract failure-inducing pattern.

generalize(self) -> Dict[str, Any]: Generalize arguments seen. For each function argument, produce an abstract failure-inducing input that characterizes the set of inputs for which the function fails.
__enter__(self) -> Any: Called at begin of `with` block. Turn tracing on.
__exit__(self, exc_tp:Type, exc_value:BaseException, exc_traceback:traceback) -> Union[bool, NoneType]: Called at end of `with` block. Turn tracing off.

class TreeGeneralizer: Determine which parts of a derivation tree can be generalized.

__init__(self, grammar:Dict[str, List[Union[str, Tuple[str, Dict[str, Any]]]]], tree:Tuple[str, Union[List[Any], NoneType]], test:Callable, max_tries_for_generalization:int=10, **kwargs:Any) -> None: Constructor. `grammar` and `tree` are as in `TreeMutator`. `test` is a function taking a string that either * raises an exception, indicating test failure; * or not, indicating test success. `max_tries_for_generalization` is the number of times an instantiation has to fail before it is generalized.
can_generalize(self, path:List[int], tree:Union[Tuple[str, Union[List[Any], NoneType]], NoneType]=None) -> bool: Return True if the subtree at `path` can be generalized.

find_paths(self, predicate:Callable[[List[int], Tuple[str, Union[List[Any], NoneType]]], bool], path:Union[List[int], NoneType]=None, tree:Union[Tuple[str, Union[List[Any], NoneType]], NoneType]=None) -> List[List[int]]: Return a list of all paths for which `predicate` holds. `predicate` is a function `predicate`(`path`, `tree`), where `path` denotes a subtree in `tree`. If `predicate()` returns True, `path` is included in the returned list.
fuzz_tree(self, tree:Tuple[str, Union[List[Any], NoneType]]) -> Tuple[str, Union[List[Any], NoneType]]: Return an instantiated copy of `tree`.
generalizable_paths(self) -> List[List[int]]: Return a list of all paths whose subtrees can be generalized.
generalize(self) -> Tuple[str, Union[List[Any], NoneType]]: Returns a copy of the tree in which all generalizable subtrees are generalized (= replaced by nonterminals without children)

generalize_path(self, path:List[int], tree:Union[Tuple[str, Union[List[Any], NoneType]], NoneType]=None) -> Tuple[str, Union[List[Any], NoneType]]: Return a copy of the tree in which the subtree at `path` is generalized (= replaced by a nonterminal without children)
test_tree(self, tree:Tuple[str, Union[List[Any], NoneType]]) -> bool: Return True if testing `tree` passes, else False
